6', 68, 'Recruit and match qualified egg donors with fertility clinics to address chronic supply shortages in assisted reproductive technology.', '$2.5B-$4.2B', 'medium', 'high', 'Fertility clinics, reproductive medicine centers, and intended parents seeking egg donation services', 8, '["Donor recruitment platform charging clinics per successful match/compensation coordination", "Marketplace connecting donors with clinics, taking commission on donor compensation", "Full-service recruitment agency offering donor sourcing, screening, and legal services to fertility centers"]', NULL, '["Highly regulated industry with complex state-level legal requirements governing compensation, medical screening, and contractual obligations", "Significant compliance risk regarding FDA regulations, genetic screening protocols, and medical liability", "Reputational risk and ethical considerations around donor exploitation, informed consent, and long-term health tracking"]', '["Conduct regulatory analysis of egg donation laws across target states, including compensation limits and medical requirements", "Interview 10-15 fertility clinic directors to quantify current donor shortage severity, recruitment costs, and willingness to outsource", "Research existing competitors (e.g., donor banks, agencies) to understand market positioning, pricing, and service gaps"]', NULL, 'Fertility clinics experience prolonged patient wait times due to insufficient egg donor availability. Donor recruitment requires specialized marketing, medical compliance expertise, and clinic coordination—creating operational bottlenecks that delay treatment and limit clinic revenue capacity.', NULL, 37.8085, -122.2668, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
