12-22 01:33:52.519570', 55, 'Recruit and compensate qualified sperm donors to supply fertility clinics addressing unmet demand in assisted reproductive services.', '$2.5B-$4.2B', 'medium', 'medium', 'Sperm banks, fertility clinics, reproductive endocrinology practices, and infertility treatment centers', 6, '["Sperm bank operator with donor recruitment and compensation management", "Donor recruitment agency providing qualified candidates to fertility clinics on commission basis", "Technology platform connecting donors with clinics and managing screening/compensation workflows"]', NULL, '["Highly regulated industry requiring FDA compliance, state licensing, and rigorous donor screening protocols", "Significant liability exposure related to genetic screening, disease transmission, and identity/custody issues", "Ethical and social considerations around commodification of reproductive material and long-term donor tracking for offspring health"]', '["Research existing sperm bank operations and regulatory requirements (FDA guidance, state reproductive tissue laws)", "Interview 10-15 fertility clinic directors to quantify donor shortage severity and willingness to pay for recruitment services", "Analyze competitor sperm banks (Fairfax Cryobank, California Cryobank, etc.) to identify service gaps and market positioning opportunities"]', NULL, 'Sperm banks and fertility clinics struggle to maintain adequate inventory of donor sperm to meet patient demand. Qualified donors must undergo extensive medical screening, genetic testing, and repeated visits over 6+ months, creating a labor-intensive and costly recruitment process. Current compensation structures ($1,000 per completed donation cycle) are insufficient to attract and retain enough donors relative to market demand.', NULL, 37.7813, -122.4167, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
